<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pedro Ross: May Day Celebrations Too Costly </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pedro Ross: May Day Celebrations Too Costly </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0704154794 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0704154794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Workers Federation Secretary General Pedro 
Ross Leal has announced that there will be people's marches on 
the occasion of 1 May only in the municipalities of Pinar del 
Rio, Artemisa, and Matanzas and in one of the two capitals of 
Havana Province [sentence as heard]. Here is journalist 
Diosdado Maso with further details on the 1 May celebrations: 
  [Begin Maso recording] Ross explained that the reason the 
marches of the militant Cuban people are not being held in both 
the capital and municipalities is the economic situation the 
country is going through. How can we hold ceremonies when there 
are workplaces and sugar mills that need the labor force and the 
resources we might use in holding such ceremonies? Ross gave the 
construction of the two grandstands at the national ceremony 
held every year in Revolution Square as an example. He said just 
one of these grandstands uses up more than seven cubic meters of 
wood, without counting the nails, the fuel, the fabric -- in 
short, great expense. 
  Concerning the political justification for not holding the 
march of the militant Cuban people here in the capital, Ross 
said that holding the special session of the National Assembly, 
where the suggestions made by the workers during the Parliaments 
in the Workplace were discussed, is the best acknowledgement of 
the Cuban trade-union movement by its government and its people. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

