<H3> <TI>   Alarcon, ANPP Leadership Visit Granma Province </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alarcon, ANPP Leadership Visit Granma Province </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0704205594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0704205594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ricardo Alarcon, president of the National Assembly 
of the People's Government [ANPP], has stressed the great 
efforts by the people of Granma in confronting the current 
situation, and their profound patriotic and revolutionary faith. 
Alarcon and other ANPP leaders participated in a three-day visit 
to the province, along with seven of its work commissions, to 
inspect preparations for the forthcoming report the province 
will render to the ANPP. 
  [Begin Alarcon recording] [Words indistinct] I must stress 
that beyond a doubt, if we seek that part of Cuba where the 
roots, heart, and struggle of the fatherland have been alive for 
over 120 years, we must immediately think of the Cuban region we 
today call Granma Province. 
  Here one finds many people aware of the progress report 
process, aware of what is being done in this regard. It is a 
stimulus, something that helps boost the tasks conducted by the 
provincial organizations, things they were doing anyhow. This 
process, however, helps to give a certain impetus to the entire 
collective effort. [end recording] 
  The ANPP presidency stressed the fact that in Granma, over 
500 low-cost houses have been built of a semester plan for 
1,000, and the fact that the province has confirmed it will 
fulfill its current sugar production plan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

