    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities monitored through 7 April. 
  The Mercantil Bank has issued commercial papers worth $3 
million on the international market. The papers were bought by 
U.S. investors and financial organizations. This is the first 
time a Peruvian bank carried out such an operation on a 
short-term basis. (Lima EXPRESO in Spanish 25 Mar 94 p A35) 
  On 25 March, representatives of the State Petroleum Agency 
and Shell signed an agreement designed to conduct studies on the 
production and marketing of gas in the Camisea reserves, the 
results of which will be known in May 1995. (Lima LA REPUBLICA 
in Spanish 26 Mar 94 p 3) 

