<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Candidates on PRI Candidate Zedillo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Candidates on PRI Candidate Zedillo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0704230994 Mexico City EL FINANCIERO in Spanish 4 Apr 94 p 
46 </F>

<F P=103> PA0704230994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City EL FINANCIERO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "This Is How the Opposition Views the </F>
New PRI Candidate"] 
  [Text] Opposition candidates have reacted with diverse 
opinions to the emergence of Ernesto Zedillo Ponce de Leon as 
substitute standard bearer for the PRI [Institutional 
Revolutionary Party] to the presidency. Presidential hopefuls 
Diego Fernandez de Cevallos, of the National Action Party (PAN); 
Cuauhtemoc Cardenas Solorzano, of the Democratic Revolutionary 
Party (PRD); Jorge Gonzalez Torres of the Mexican Green 
Ecologist Party (PVEM); Marcela Lombardo Otero of the Popular 
Socialist Party (PPS); Pablo Emilio Madero of the Mexican 
Democratic Party (PDM); Rafael Aguilar Talamantes, of the 
Cardenist Front for National Reconftruction Party (PFCRN); 
Cecilia Soto Gonzalez of the Labor Party, and Alvaro Perez 
Trevino of the Authentic Party of the Mexican Revolution (PARM) 
said the following: 
  Diego Fernandez de Cevallos: Ernesto Zedillo "is a 
respectable and honest person who will certainly play a good 
role as presidential hopeful for his party. I now have an 
adversary again and will strive for the presidency." 
  Cuauhtemoc Cardenas: "Perhaps now more than ever, he is the 
presidential candidate of continuity." Hopefully, despite how 
he was chosen, "it will be a clean and straighforward election." 
  Jorge Gonzalez Torres: "Zedillo represents the continuity of 
a sinking ship and of something that failed." The new candidate 
"bases his political campaign in the image of Colosio, because 
he lacks his own personality." 
  Marcela Lombardo: "The choice of Zedillo falls within the 
same democratic trend presented by Colosio, because it follows 
the same objectives and the same proposals of Colosio." 
  Pablo Emilio Madero: "I hope that Zedillo's participation in 
the elections will be pure and clear, conforming to reality. It 
is hoped he will assume the responsibility inherited from 
Colosio of talking to all sectors." 
  Rafael Aguilar Talamantes: "Zedillo's participation will 
raise the stature of the electoral race and will certainly 
guarantee that it will be civilized, tolerant, and respectful of 
all the candidates." 
  Cecilia Soto: "All the contendors deserve respect. Zedillo 
will be an important contender. It is hoped he will embrace 
Colosio's positions." 
  Alvaro Perez Trevino: "The proposals made to the people and 
the political line of Ernesto Zedillo will differ substantially 
from the proposals made by Luis Donaldo Colosio." 

</TEXT>

