<H3> <TI>   Candidate Galindo on Antidrug Struggle </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Candidate Galindo on Antidrug Struggle </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0704170194 Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA in Spanish 7 
Apr 94 p A2 </F>

<F P=103> PA0704170194 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ruben Dario Diaz] </F>
  [Text] Yesterday, Samuel Lewis Galindo, presidential 
candidate of the "National Consensus Alliance," said the United 
States has assumed an irresponsible attitude by saying Panama 
has not cooperated in the antidrug-trafficking struggle. 
Galindo said efforts are being made in Panama to cooperate in 
the antidrug-trafficking struggle, and the United States has 
exaggerated in saying the contrary. "We are all intent on ending 
drug trafficking and money laundering once and for all in our 
country because it is difficult to say it will end, but it is 
incorrect to say nothing has been done," he said. 
  The presidential candidate said there are authorities who 
are 
trying to fight narcotrafficking, but he added there are groups 
of criminals who attempt to evade the security system because 
Panama is a country with long coastlines on both oceans, which 
makes it even more difficult to control. 
  Galindo also mentioned the charges against the former 
government. He said Panamanians cannot live permanently in the 
past but must learn from experiences from the past and look to 
the future; otherwise, "we will be living in the past, and the 
future will be the one that is lost." 

</TEXT>

