<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Industry Minister Fires General Director </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Industry Minister Fires General Director </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0704172194 Montevideo EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO in Spanish 
28 Mar 94 p 7 </F>

<F P=103> PY0704172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Industry Minister Eduardo Ache on 25 March fired 
Industry General Director Andres Merino Pacheco because he said 
he would resign if the government approved last week's gasoline 
price increase. Sources close to Merino Pacheco told EL 
OBSERVADOR that he sought to obtain "political profit" inside 
his faction and this annoyed Minister Ache. 
  Merino Pacheco is a nephew of Jorge Pacheco Areco, Colorado 
Party and Bettleist Union leader. He was also one of former 
Industry Minister Carlos Piran's trusted men during the previous 
government. Merino Pacheco will be replaced by current Deputy 
Secretary General Santiago Urioste, of the Herreraist faction 
[National Party faction]. 

</TEXT>

