<H3> <TI>   National Police Computers Improve Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Police Computers Improve Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20608B </F>
<F P=103> 94P20608B </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] Managua LA PRENSA in Spanish of 23 March 
1994 on page 12 reports that the National Police is installing 
specialized computer equipment which will enable it to retrieve 
information from Interpol files. The equipment was made 
available through the good offices of Interpol liaison for Latin 
America Juan Carlos Antoniassi. Ministry of Government Deputy 
Minister Frank Cesar explained that the computers will enable 
authorities to review more efficiently the legal status of 
nationalized citizens. 

</TEXT>

