<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina is in the 
Argentine capital on a two-hour [as heard] technical stopover en 
route to Peru. During this required technical stopover, Robaina 
will spend most of his time holding news conferences with Buenos 
Aires' most important newspapers and television and radio news 
networks. Exclusive interviews with Channel 13, the newspaper EL 
CLARIN, PAGINA DOCE, Radio America Dos, and the news agencies 
ANSA and EFE have already been confirmed. 
  Today, Roberto Robaina will meet with Argentine Foreign 
Minister Guido di Tella, who for work reasons will not be in 
Buenos Aires during the Cuban delegation's official visit. In 
the same way, several entrepreneurs in the pharmaceutical sphere 
have expressed great interest in speaking to Minister Robaina on 
Friday [8 April] to learn of Cuba's achievements in the area of 
biopharmaceuticals. 
  With this 48-hour technical stopover in Buenos Aires en 
route 
to Peru, the subject of Cuba; its current reality; and its 
economic, political, and social prospects are beginning to be 
heard in Argentine public opinion before the delegation's 
official visit. 

</TEXT>

