<H3> <TI>   CTC Announces Assemblies for Efficiency Process </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CTC Announces Assemblies for Efficiency Process </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0904012394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0904012394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 8 April, the National Secretariat of the Cuban 
Workers Federation [CTC] agreed to hold, for the first time, 
assemblies on economic efficiency, beginning in the second half 
of May. The first of these assemblies will be held in April and 
will examine how to fulfill the decision reached by the workers 
in the workplace assemblies, as well as new problems in the 
workplaces. The CTC National Secretariat also officially agreed 
to allocate eight million pesos a year to cover the expenses of 
the Jose Marti Pioneers Organization [OPJM]. 
  CTC Secretary General Pedro Ross Leal pointed out that the 
goal of the decision is to reduce Cuba's budget and ensure that 
children do not suffer the consequences of the special period 
and are prepared for the future. OPJM Vice President Laritza 
Diaz applauded the gesture of the CTC, which will cover the 
expenses of over 300 children's facilities nationwide to benefit 
the workers' children. 
  The CTC National Secretariat also discussed the results of 
the plenum that closed the Parliament in the Workplace process, 
and discussed the accomplishments of a group of workplaces 
nominated to receive National Emulation Vanguard status. 

</TEXT>

