<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sugarcane Weeding Levels Lag in Most Provinces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0704224194 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0704224194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The required levels of manual sugarcane weeding were 
not met by every province during the January-March quarter. This 
process does not require any type of imported resources, but 
relies fundamentally on manpower and the organization and 
mobilization of the necessary work force. 
  Holguin and Granma where the only provinces that surpassed 
their weeding goals; Havana and Camaguey Provinces followed 
close behind. However, Pinar del Rio, Villa Clara, and Ciego de 
Avila Provinces did not reach even 50 percent of the areas 
completed in their best quarters. 

</TEXT>

