<F P=100> Dominican Republic </F>
<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   COP Supports Governors Island Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    COP Supports Governors Island Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0904000794 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0904000794 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Coordinating Body of People's Organizations 
[Coordination des Organisations Populaires, COP] has reaffirmed 
its support for the Governors Island agreement, the only valid 
framework to get the country out of the crisis, according to 
COP. It thinks the formation of an ad hoc government would just 
plunge the country into even more chaos. Let us listen to an 
unidentified COP spokesman: 
  [Begin unidentified spokesman recording, in Creole] Our 
position in COP regarding the ad hoc government that is being 
discussed today is that this idea is not viable. It offers 
nothing toward resolving the country's crisis. We in COP have 
always said there is no solution but the Governors Island 
agreement for resolving the country's crisis, because the 
Governors Island agreement is an agreement of principle signed 
by General Cedras and President Aristide in the presence of the 
international community to resolve the country's crisis. 
  We think that so long as stalling maneuvers are aimed at 
preventing the reactivation of the Governors Island agreement, 
the country's crisis will never be resolved. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

