<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alleged Assassination Plot Leader Surrenders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alleged Assassination Plot Leader Surrenders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0804215594 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 0100 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0804215594 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tegucigalpa, 7 Apr (ACAN-EFE) -- The presumed 
mastermind of the plot to assassinate Honduran President Carlos 
Roberto Reina has voluntarily surrendered to a court in this 
capital on 7 April, a judicial source has confirmed. 
  Luis Hernandez Sosa, 30, surprised the security corps when 
he 
arrived unexpectedly at the First Lower Criminal Court in 
Tegucigalpa at 1600 local (2200 GMT) accompanied by human rights 
leaders. 
  Sosa is linked to a plot to assassinate President Reina 
uncovered on 13 March when Nicaraguan citizen Luis Rene Quintero 
confessed his participation to the Nicaraguan Government 
Ministry. 
  According to Quintero, Honduran Hernandez Sosa hired him 
along with Nicaraguan citizens Santiago Rivas and Roger Arguello 
to kill President Reina for $400,000, as confirmed by Honduran 
military spokesman Colonel Napoleon Santos Aguilar. 
  Members of the Human Rights Commissioner's Office and of the 
court confirmed to ACAN-EFE that Hernandez turned himself in to 
the First Lower Criminal Court in Tegucigalpa. In a brief 
statement to judicial reporters, Hernandez said he is "innocent" 
of all charges. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

