GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1104010294 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Violeta Barrios de Chamorro's 4-7 April 
official visit to Mexico resulted in the signing of a 
$10-million credit agreement as well as ensuring cooperation 
assistance programs in the health, social, welfare, and 
technical sectors. 
  Nicaragua and Mexico agreed that a free trade agreement 
between both nations would be signed before year's end. 
Likewise, the president indicated that both nations agreed that 
their respective finance ministers would meet shortly to discuss 
Nicaragua's debt with Mexico which it expects to repay with 
assets. [as heard] 
  After publicly expressing her gratitude to President Carlos 
Salinas de Gortari for the attention received during her visit, 
as well as to all those persons who expressed their concern for 
her alleged fainting spell, she proceeded to explain all the 
activities carried out while in Mexico. The president also 
expressed enormous satisfaction with the results of her trip. 

</TEXT>

