<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Human Rights Ombudsman Cites Antidemocracy Plot </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Human Rights Ombudsman Cites Antidemocracy Plot </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0804184694 Guatemala City SIGLO VEINTIUNO in Spanish 7 Apr 
94 p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PA0804184694 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City SIGLO VEINTIUNO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In an urgent communique following the attack against 
Deputy Chinchilla Vega, Human Rights Ombudsman Jorge Mario 
Garcia Laguardia reported the existence of an antidemocracy 
conspiracy and asked the government to use the constitutional 
mechanisms to stop the continuation of these events. 
  Upon condemning the attack against the deputy, Garcia said 
this incident demonstrates an attempt is being made to end the 
democratic system in the country. He added the attack represents 
an unjustifiable action, just like the assassination of 
Magistrate Epaminondas Gonzalez at a time when the government 
and URNG [Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity] signed a 
global human rights accord. 
  The human rights ombudsman demanded the government of the 
Republic end this series of events aimed at disrupting the 
democratic regime. He asked the government to implement the 
constitutional mechanisms; that is, to have security forces 
comply with their duty. 

</TEXT>

