<H3> <TI>   EZLN Leader Killed; Marcos Confirms Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EZLN Leader Killed; Marcos Confirms Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0904214694 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 2100 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0904214694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 9 Apr (DPA) -- A leader of the Zapatist 
National Liberation Army (EZLN) was killed yesterday by a 
rancher in Altamirano municipality, Chiapas State, the EZLN 
Clandestine Revolutionary Committee reported today. 
  In a statement published by the EXCELSIOR News Agency, 
guerrilla spokesman Subcommander Marcos said this action 
contradicts the alleged climate of peace to which Manuel Camacho 
Solis, commissioner for peace and reconciliation in Chiapas, has 
referred. Nevertheless, the cease-fire will be maintained. 
  According to the statement, the EZLN leader went with a 
companion to see a parcel of land to farm. When they arrived at 
the site, they were met with shots fired by the ranch owner's 
son. The leader's companion was wounded. 

</TEXT>

