<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   EZLN Members Killed in Clashes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EZLN Members Killed in Clashes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1104141394 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1310 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1104141394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1310 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Five members of the Zapatist National Liberation 
Army [EZLN] were killed in a clash with cattlemen in Comitan, 
Chiapas. In San Cristobal de las Casas, EZLN forces demanded the 
release of 21 civilians accused of being EZLN members from Cerro 
Hueco Prison. Patricial Serrano filed this report: 
  [Serrano] Five EZLN members were killed during three clashes 
in Comitan Municipality, Chiapas States. The incidents occurred 
when EZLN members trespassed on the ranchers' properties to 
rustle cattle. The ranchers reacted immediately to save their 
property and the lives of their families. 
  Upon being informed of these events, Subcommander Marcos 
confirmed from an undisclosed location in Lacandon jungle that 
indeed two [number as heard] EZLN supporters were killed in 
clashes with ranchers. 
  Meanwhile in San Cristobal de las Casas, the EZLN demanded 
the release of 21 civilians from El Cerezo de Cerro Hueco Prison 
who were arrested on suspicion of being EZLN members. From that 
place, Subcommander Marcos also said that keeping these innocent 
individuals in jail is an obstacle to peace talks with the 
federal government. Marcos stated that the indiscriminate 
arrest of civilians on unfounded charges that they are members 
of the EZLN is an arbitrary action. 
  Ceremonies, parades, marches, and festivities were held in 
Chiapas on Sunday to commemorate the 75th anniversary of the 
death of revolutionary leader Emiliano Zapata. 

</TEXT>

