<H3> <TI>   Peasants Plan Protests in Chiapas To Mark Zapata's Death </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peasants Plan Protests in Chiapas To Mark Zapata's Death </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1004161394 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1514 
GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1004161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Face to Face" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Today marks the 75th anniversary of Emiliano 
Zapata's death. There will be a number of ceremonies, including 
one in Morelos State. The president will attend this morning's 
ceremony in Cuernavaca, Morelos State. There will be another in 
Zacatepec this afternoon. Cuauhtemoc Cardenas, Party of the 
Democratic Revolution presidential candidate, will attend the 
ceremony in Zacatepec. 
  As for the anniversary, there will be a demonstration in 
Mexico City. Some 70 peasant organizations will stage a march, 
which will end in El Zocalo, downtown Mexico City. They will 
declare a seven-day sitdown strike here to demand the repeal of 
Article 27 of the Constitution. 
  Meanwhile, there will be some celebrations, quote, in 
Chiapas, unquote. A report in REFORMA newspaper adds: The 
Indian and Peasant State Committee will stage marches, conduct 
motorcades, seize land, hold regional sitdown strikes, take over 
public buildings, and hold regional gatherings in the 
municipalities of Tapachula, Palenque, San Cristobal de las 
Casas, and Comitan. This is how the 75th anniversary of 
Emiliano Zapata's death will be commemorated. 

</TEXT>

