  [Text] Members of peasant, Indian, and mass organizations 
from various states marched today from the Altar to the 
Fatherland Monument to the Zocalo to mark the 75th anniversary 
of the death of General Emiliano Zapata. The march, which began 
at 1110 and ended at 1420, was held without incident. Walls 
along the route were painted with social demands. The march 
passed along important Mexico City avenues such as Reforma, 
Insurgentes, and Juarez. The police reported that some 300 
officers were deployed along the route to maintain order and 
divert traffic. 

