<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authorities Release One Suspect </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authorities Release One Suspect </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1104042294 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0229 GMT 11 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1104042294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Mexico City, 10 Apr (NOTIMEX) -- The Special 
Assistant Prosecutor's Office in charge of clearing up the 
murder of presidential candidate Luis Donaldo Colosio reported 
today that one of the suspects in the case was released with 
reservations and that formal jail warrants were issued for two 
others. 
  The Attorney General's Office of the Republic (PGR) added 
that Jose Rodolfo Rivapalacio Tinajero was released under "legal 
reservations," due to lack of evidence of his participation in 
Colosio's murder, which took place on 23 March. 
  In an official communique, the PGR added that formal jail 
warrants were issued for Rodolfo Mayoral Esquer and Vicente 
Mayoral Valenzuela, as being probably responsible in the murder, 
to the degree of co-participants as aides or accessories to the 
crime. 
  The Mayorals, father and son, were acquitted on charges of 
criminal association due to a lack of evidence; nevertheless, if 
new evidence is found the case could be reopened for the same 
crime. 
  Included in this case are Tranquilino Sanchez Vanegas and 
Mario Aburto Martinez, perpetrators of the crime that took place 
in Tijuana, Baja California State, in northwestern Mexico. 
  The four individuals remain incarcerated in the Almoloya 
Penitentiary in the State of Mexico, 90 km from this capital 
where they are to be processed. In the Rivapalacio Tinajero 
case, the Attorney General's Office made him responsible for 
incorporating Tranquilino Sanchez Vanegas, Vicente Mayoral 
Valenzuela, and Rodolfo Mayoral Esquer into the group he 
organized, apparently to keep order during the Lomas Taurinas 
political event. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

