<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armed Forces Deny Restriction of Press Freedom </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armed Forces Deny Restriction of Press Freedom </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0804184994 Asuncion NOTICIAS in Spanish 7 Apr 94 p 19 </F>
<F P=103> PY0804184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion NOTICIAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Sergio Lopez, a member of the Chamber of 
Deputies Defense Committee, yesterday visited the Armed Forces 
Command building where he met with Colonel Carlos Medina 
Monjagata, the Military Forces' public relations director. 
  Lopez was accompanied by Deputy Carlos Riveros and Senator 
Fernando Pfannl. The visitors wanted to clarify the incident on 
5 April when NOTICIAS photographer Ismael Villalba was held for 
one hour after he committed "the sin" of photographing a 
conversation between Lopez and soldier Crispulo Sanchez. 
  A captain whose last name is Galeano and other two officers 
were also arrested as a consequence of this incident. 
  "The colonel told us there had been a misunderstanding in 
the 
case of the reporter and explained that the Armed Forces does 
not intend to restrict freedom of the press," the deputy said. 
  Regarding the arrest of the captain and the other officers, 
the colonel said they were arrested for not carrying out the 
already famous "order from above." The deputy, however, could 
not say who gave that order. 
  "It seems that the order was that I could not speak with the 
soldier either despite the colonel's remark that the soldier was 
at my disposal. Those were the two reasons for the arrest of 
Galeano and his comrades," the deputy said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

