<H3> <TI>   Senators, Party Leaders Criticize Resolution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senators, Party Leaders Criticize Resolution </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Mayor Blames Resolution Authors </H4>

<F P=102> FL1104214994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1700 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1104214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Evans Paul, mayor of Port-au-Prince and National 
Front for Change and Democracy spokesman, criticizes the authors 
of the resolution for enforcement of Article 149 of the 
Constitution. It is the coup d'etat logic that continues, 
Port-au-Prince Mayor Evans Paul told the Haitian Press Agency 
regarding the 10 April vote by the Senate [office] led by 
Bernard Sansaricq for a resolution relating to the reenforcement 
of the Constitution. It is a masquerade without legal 
foundation, by individuals with no electoral legitimacy, who do 
not respect any logic, he adds, explaining that their objective 
is to work for the ruin of the people and to guarantee 
themselves continued illicit wealth. 
  Paul further stated that the international community will 
not 
back this undertaking, which is already doomed to failure and 
which will most likely result in reinforcement of the sanctions. 
  After accusing the authors of the resolution and their 
allies 
of responsibility for the misfortunes of the country, Mr. Paul 
noted that no one has acknowledged Sansaricq as president of the 
Senate. Neither have the parliamentarians stemming from the 
contested 18 January [1993] elections, whose fate depends on the 
verdict of the arbitration committee provided for by the Haitian 
Constitution, been acknowledged as senators. 

</TEXT>

