<H3> <TI>   Public Participation in Loan Market Drops </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Public Participation in Loan Market Drops </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0704222494 </F>
<F P=103> PA0704222494 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] San Jose LA REPUBLICA in Spanish on 24 
March on page 12A reports that public sector participation in 
the loan market dropped from 43 percent to 20 percent during 
1993, leaving the other 80 percent to the private sector. Jorge 
Corrales, president of the Central Bank of Costa Rica, reported 
that services received the larger portion of the funds, thus 
showing a decrease in primary and secondary activities. He 
explained that this behavior is consistent with current economic 
trends, where services tend to show the greatest movement. 

</TEXT>

