<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Visits Tunisia, Morocco </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Visits Tunisia, Morocco </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1204124894 Buenos Aires LA NACION in Spanish 11 Apr 94 p 
19--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY1204124894 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires LA NACION </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Argentine Foreign Minister Guido Di Tella travelled 
on 10 April to Tunis, where he will meet with Tunisian and PLO 
authorities. According to information obtained by LA NACION, Di 
Tella will discuss the status of the PLO's representation in 
Buenos Aires with his PLO colleague [Faruk] Qaddumi. 
  The foreign minister will also meet with Argentine 
ambassadors posted in Middle East and North African countries in 
order to coordinate diplomatic actions that are to be 
undertaken. Di Tella will then travel to Morocco to participate 
in the GATT meeting that is to be held in Marrakech. After this 
meeting he will remain in Morocco for an official visit at the 
invitation of his colleague Abdellatif Filali. 

