<H3> <TI>   Senate Patents Bill Report To Be Ready 22 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senate Patents Bill Report To Be Ready 22 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1304002994 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
12 Apr 94 Business and Economic Section p3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY1304002994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese and Economic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Economic Report" column by Miriam Lage] </F>
  [Text] Senator Jose Richa, the rapporteur of the patents 
draft law, on 11 April had lunch with Industry and Commerce 
Minister Elcio Alvares, who will be leaving for Geneva to sign 
the final terms of the Uruguay GATT Round. Richa informed 
Alvares that his report on the patents draft law will be ready 
by 22 April. After dispensing with further public hearings, the 
report will be submitted to the Senate Economic Committee. In 
one month, the Senate plenum could vote on the draft law. 

</TEXT>

